        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/{size}/34172_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-04T00:52:09.163Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This fits under several existing feature requests:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"9731\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/34f0e0/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/todo-or-check-list/9731\">Todo or Check list</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    For the last days, I realized that my wife is using my whatsapp profile as a note reminder. She wrote shopping list and send it to me as a message. I mean it is a good way to remember smth other than Calendar. Calendar is smth people dont really use it. If they are not in any business or eager to use it personally. \nThen, a timed message with the option check marks can be very fancy. For example, in order to send a message to my wife as a list, I can send a message to myself and create a timed m‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"57639\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/matrixrave/48/44687_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/pin-a-message-to-top-of-chat/57639\">Pin a message to top of chat</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Currently to my knowledge it is not possible to pin a message in a chat or a group chat to the top so it stays visible for everybody. This could be handy especially for groups if you want to remind group members of something, so they dont lose the message. \nThis could be displayed right underneath the info bar with name and profile picture, using a little pin to indicate that the message is pinned. \nFor reference: Telegram has a feature like this and WhatsApp just announced it in their latest re‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"44267\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/shadowber/48/30410_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/allow-notes-seen-only-by-you-in-groups/44267\">Allow notes seen only by you in groups</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    So I got this idea from a WhatsApp mistake. WhatsApp just integrated (copied from signal) emoji reactions (though it‚Äôs limited to 6). While testing it my brother and I noticed a bug where in a moderator post only group it brings up the text field when using reactions. But when you write something it posts it but only you can see it with a warning that you can‚Äôt post. That made me think about being able to write notes to yourself (that are clearly marked as such, making it easy to find) that are ‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n<aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"6004\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/sdsdsasad12312/48/2414_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/bookmarks-favorites-starred-messages/6004\">Bookmarks / favorites / starred messages</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Add a feature that lets users favorite messages and save them into a list that they can check later on. It‚Äôs fundamental when you wanna find special moments /memories / pictures and stuff.\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"44267\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/shadowber/48/30410_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/allow-notes-seen-only-by-you-in-groups/44267\">Allow notes seen only by you in groups</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    So I got this idea from a WhatsApp mistake. WhatsApp just integrated (copied from signal) emoji reactions (though it‚Äôs limited to 6). While testing it my brother and I noticed a bug where in a moderator post only group it brings up the text field when using reactions. But when you write something it posts it but only you can see it with a warning that you can‚Äôt post. That made me think about being able to write notes to yourself (that are clearly marked as such, making it easy to find) that are ‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
